  "text": "Transient imaging has recently emerged as a vibrant, exciting area of research. Being able to analyze light transport at picosecond scale has already helped gain a better understanding of the complexities of light propagation [ . In this paper, we offer a novel contribution by visualizing relativistic effects of time-varying radiance. Beyond the pure scientific interest of advancing the field of relativistic visualization, our work has direct applications in education and even games (see for instance OpenRelativity from the MIT Game Lab [CITATION_1] ). Additionally, it can also contribute to recent works which have set the ground for a time-resolved framework for light transport simulation [JMM * 14].",
